MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

01-454. Hughes v. Calabrese.

In Prohibition. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of prohibition. Upon consideration of respondent’s motion to dismiss and on determination pursuant to S.Ct.Prac.R. X(5),

IT IS ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.

F.E. Sweeney, J., would grant an alternative writ staying Part 1A of the trial court’s temporary restraining order. Douglas, J., not participating.
